devdoc.author: victaphu
devdoc.details: On-Chain reporting of a single metric and its count defined by a key and a category.  It will store each in a bucket denoted by the {Report}-{getReportingPeriodFor} function,  which defines a bucket given a timestamp. The report is configured for weekly reporting,  with a week starting on Sunday. Override the {getReportingPeriodFor} to derive your own reporting period. Note Use the provided API to update the global report or the latest reports. When updating the latest reports, the global report is also updated. Designed as real-time reporting. A global report keeps track of overall accumulated values. Note no overflow has been added ... something to be mindful of

getLatestReport().details: get the latest report at the highest level. includes key dimension breakdown note returns data for the next level, use the keys to query further

returns.count: current total count for the overall report
returns.counts: all the counts that have been accumulated so far
returns.keys: a list of key dimensions. sums, counts and keys have same length and indexed accordingly
returns.sums: all the sums that have been accumulated so far

getLatestReport(bytes).details: get the latest report for a key dimension note returns data for the next level, use the categories to query further

params.key: the key dimension which we want to report on

returns.count: current total count for the overall report
returns.counts: all the counts that have been accumulated so far
returns.keys: a list of key dimensions. sums, counts and keys have same length and indexed accordingly
returns.sums: all the sums that have been accumulated so far

getLatestReport(bytes,bytes).details: get the latest report for a key and category dimension

params.key: the key dimension which we want to report on

returns.count: current total count for the overall report

getLatestReportingPeriod().details: get the latest reporting period given the block timestamp. Return a normalised value based on timestamp. By default we return normalised by week

returns.reportPeriod: the normalised report period for the latest timestamp

getReportForPeriod(uint256).details: get the report for a given period. supply 0 for the argument to get the global report note returns data for the next level, use the keys to query further

params.period: the period for which we want to retrieve the data

returns.count: current total count for the overall report
returns.counts: all the counts that have been accumulated so far
returns.keys: a list of key dimensions. sums, counts and keys have same length and indexed accordingly
returns.sums: all the sums that have been accumulated so far

getReportForPeriod(uint256,bytes).details: get the report for a given period and key dimension. supply 0 for the argument to get the global report note returns data for the next level, use the keys to query further

params.key: the key dimension which we want to report on
params.period: the period for which we want to retrieve the data

returns.count: current total count for the overall report
returns.counts: all the counts that have been accumulated so far
returns.keys: a list of key dimensions. sums, counts and keys have same length and indexed accordingly
returns.sums: all the sums that have been accumulated so far

getReportForPeriod(uint256,bytes,bytes).details: get the report for a given period and key dimension. supply 0 for the argument to get the global report note returns data for the next level, use the keys to query further

params.category: the category dimension which we want to report on
params.key: the key dimension which we want to report on
params.period: the period for which we want to retrieve the data

returns.count: current total count for the overall report

getReportPeriodFor(uint256).details: this function will take a timestamp and normalise it to a value By default reports are normalised to closest start of the week, so this function will help generate weekly reports
